Hyper text transfer protocol (HTTP) primary communication protocol for web applications.  set of rules that govern how computers are supposed to talk to eachother . The client/local machine sends a request to the server (remote machine), and the server machine has a response that it sends back to the client .  The server always responds with a status code: 1xx -> Informational, 2xx Succss (200), 3xx Redirection. 4xx Client error (404 page not found), 5xx Server Error. Each request sent by the client goes through a header (like he first few lines of the request that gets sent), The start line of the header e.g. GET/background.png HTTP/1.0 , has the method (GET), the target (background.png) which exact fileare we trying to locate and the thrid parameter is the verion (HTTP/1.0) verion ogf http we are using. The next part of the header is the header which has addditional information about the request e.g. User agent mosilla/5.0  , what web browser whe are using etc, the body of the request is typically empty and theserver uses the body to send back our files. The serve also uses header files, the start line e.g. HTTP/1.1 404 Not Found , whcih has the version and the status code and the status text.  HTTP is a stateless protocol, connection between devices are not maintained during interactions. it is based on TCP/IP protocol, 

